Marcus was taken aback for a moment. Was she flirting with him? Or was he entirely misreading the situation. They’d barely spoken, and she was clearly so much younger than he was, but that mischievous expression left him off balance.
“Uh, thanks,” he stammered, uncertain of how to respond. 
“Oh wow,” her grin turned a little more lascivious, “and shy too. Definitely too bad we didn’t run into each other sooner.”
“Uh, yeah,” he could feel his face heating up, “definitely.” Marcus noticed with an odd feeling of relief that his stop was next. “Maybe we’ll meet again another time under… less constrained circumstances.” He had no problem admitting to himself that he was running away. He just wasn’t sure how to handle aggressive women who were barely older than his own daughter.
</Text>
