            <Title>Awakening</Title>
            <Text>Marcus woke up slowly, his head feeling as though it were wrapped in wool. His mouth was dry and he felt cold tile beneath his bare back. Which made no sense as the last thing he remembered was being in a carpeted elevator and wearing his vest and a tee shirt. He groggily opened his eyes only to be confronted with yet another screen in the center of his vision.

Welcome to the Multiverse.
Mana adaptation process successful!
Unexpected race evolution detected! 
Customizing Introduction sequence…
Initializing Introduction, please stand by…
Introduction period begins in 0:59:59

Beyond the semi-transparent screen, he could see that he was lying on his back staring up at a white ceiling. The room was well lit, but with no clear source of illumination. 
Groaning, he forced himself to a sitting position, which allowed him to take in the rest of the room he was in. The room was entirely white and completely empty aside from himself. Smooth white ceiling and walls, cold white tile floor. Even the light in the room seemed to be a soft white color. No distinguishing features anywhere that he could he see.
And he was naked. No sign of his clothes, his phone, his cane or even an entrance to the strange room. He rubbed his hands over his face and frowned. The skin on his face felt… different. Strange. There were patches on his cheeks and brow around his eyes that felt rough and almost scaly. He frantically felt around the rest of his face, and thankfully nothing else there felt wrong. Then he looked at the rest of his body, noticing patches of dark brown to almost black scales on his torso, arms and legs. 
“What the ever-loving fuck!” he scrambled to his feet in a panic.
And that wasn’t all, his fingers were slightly longer and more slender than he remembered and tipped in hard sharp talons. His toes were tipped in somewhat shorter versions of the same. Even the skin that wasn’t scaly looked rougher and had darkened somewhat to an almost sandy tan color. 
And his body, aside from his face and head, was hairless!
“Your mana adaptation activated dormant traits in your pattern,” a calm, feminine voice said from behind him. “This resulted in changes to your physical and metaphysical bodies.”
Marcus whirled to find a tall, slender woman behind him where no one had been moments before. Like him, she had patches of scales around her eyes, on her forehead and down the visible portions of her arms. Unlike him, her scales were the vibrant green of living vegetation. He also noticed her eyes resembled those of a snake or lizard, with a vertical slit instead of a round pupil.
It was at this point that he realized the screen he’d been seeing had vanished. “What the hell! What’s going on here?” he gasped out, instinctively covering his dangly bits with his hands at seeing the woman. “Where am I? Where are my clothes? Who are you?” His heart was hammering in his chest
“What’s going on is your universe is being integrated into the Multiverse by the System. You are currently in the Introduction sequence, an experience intended to help you understand the changes to your world and prepare you for the tutorial.” She spoke in that same calm, even tone, showing no emotional reaction to his outburst.  “Your clothes and belongings were destroyed by exposure to the intense mana required to trigger your mana adaptation. And I am your Guide to the Introduction.”

