            <Title>Mental Evaluation - Willpower</Title>
            <Text>Rest period duration remaining 0:09:59

The Guide stiffened and began explaining the final evaluation cycle. “This final cycle will be focused on your willpower and ability to concentrate on a single task without distraction.” She paused, clearly receiving information from the System. “In your case, this task will be complicated by the fact that you will need to use your mana control as well.”
“When the test begins, a sphere of mana aspected to the concepts of heaviness and solidity will form just below the ceiling. Your task is to focus your mana control and keep that sphere from hitting the floor.”
Marcus blinked. “I assume this will be harder than it sounds?”
“Most likely yes. It will be roughly akin to lifting a solid object with nothing but your will and your mana control.” She nodded. “Further, as time goes on, the environment around you will produce distractions in an attempt to break your concentration. Any other questions?”
“What happens when it inevitably does hit the floor?”
“Then it will vanish and reappear near the ceiling so you can try again.”
“And when I reach mental exhaustion?” 
“Then you will begin the second phase of this cycle: resistance training.”
“Resisting what exactly?” He asked hesitantly.
“Pain,” she replied bluntly. “Pain resistance is the only passive way to test or improve willpower, a fact you should be well aware of given the strength of your will at this point.”
Marcus groaned aloud. “I was afraid you were gonna say that.”
He settled into his meditation position and focused his mana senses on the ceiling, waiting for the sphere to manifest. After a few minutes, he received a notification as the sphere began to coalesce. 

Beginning Final Evaluation Cycle.
Current Cycle duration remaining 05:59:59

Concentrating, he focused his will on the sphere, trying to infuse it with his intent only to find that the sphere resisted. Fuck! If he had to try to fight through that much resistance, his mental energy wouldn’t last long at all. He needed another idea. Releasing his will, he pushed his senses into the sphere, trying to understand it. Its aspects made it feel like a solid object to his mana senses. And he abruptly felt it begin to fall. It didn’t fall as fast as he feared it would, because it only had a semblance of mass rather the reality of it. 
He needed something to catch it with… something else with a similar sense of solidity. He mimicked the feel of the sphere and envisioned a cupped hand beneath the sphere, holding it up. Quickly, he gathered mana into his imagined hand, infused it with the barest modicum of his will,  and pushed upward against the sphere. The hand was just solid enough and managed to slow the descent, but not stop it. He gathered more mana, increasing the solidity of his mental construct and increasing his infusion of will by the tiniest increments he could manage until the sphere drifted to a stop a scant three feet from the floor.

Congratulations! Skill Learned: Beginner Telekinesis (Tier 1) Level 1! Willpower has increased by 1!
Congratulations! Skill Learned: Beginner Concentration (Tier 1) Level 1! Willpower has increased by 1!

He suppressed a grin. If this was all he had to do then this would be a lot easier than the Guide made it sound, he could hold this almost indefinitely. The strain on his willpower and ability to focus were so slight it didn’t feel like he was expending any mental energy at all. In fact, it required so little energy that he was easily able to raise his telekinetic hand and lift the sphere back to the ceiling effortlessly.
