Marcus brought his focus back to the present. Goals were all well and good, but that one was a long way off and he needed to lay a foundation for it here and now. He needed his head in the game. “What’s the deal with these training periods you mentioned?”
“Once it begins I will spend the next 10 hours teaching you. We will start with a basic skill everyone in the Multiverse learns and from there, it will be up to you. Most use their first training period to get System recognition of skills they already possess and their second to learn things they think will help them survive in the post-System world.”
“Okay, one last question before we run out of time then, how does one increase their race tier?” He asked.
“By walking their path,” she answered. “This means progressing in both your class and profession as well as your overall level. Your race tier is limited by all three. Once you have raised your class and profession to the next tier and have enough levels, you’ll receive a quest to complete to raise your race tier.”
“So, 10 levels and get my profession and class to tier 2 and then I can raise my race tier?”
“No. 20 levels not 10.” She corrected him, before explaining. “These levels work a little differently in two ways. First, they do not reset when your race tier increases. Second, you need to gain ten times as many levels as the tier you’re trying to reach.”
“So level 20 for tier 2, level 30 for tier 3?” He hoped that’s what she meant, but was pretty sure that it was not going to be that easy.
“No. Level 2o for tier 2, level 50 for tier 3, level 90 for tier 4, level 140 for tier 5, and so on until you reach the tier 9 at level 440,” she gave him a sympathetic look. “And then you would still need 100 more levels to begin to seek godhood.”
“Well, that certainly explains why it takes so long to reach godhood,” he said with a grimace. “I also assume each level is harder to get than the one before it?”
“Yes. You only gain experience toward your level by facing a legitimate challenge, such as killing a beast close to you in level, or using your profession to craft something appropriate to your level. Repeating the same tasks, such as slaying the same kind of beast repeatedly will eventually begin to result in diminishing returns.”
