“Your progress has been quite impressive so far,” the Guide stated as he closed his status screen. “Your performance thus far is likely to unlock some interesting paths for you, especially if you perform this well in the final evaluation.”
“I assume the next set of evaluations will focus on mental attributes?” He was pretty sure he knew the answer, but it never hurt to verify.
“Essentially yes,” she replied. “It will put you through a series of tests and trials meant to instill some skills that will improve your mental stats as they develop. While these trials will be considerably longer than any of the previous evaluations, they will be far less physically demanding for the most part.” The Guide tilted her head as she considered him again. “You will, however want to recoup your mana and stamina as you will need mana for the first evaluation cycle.”
