Mana: 133/238

Without the help of the staff, each bolt he used consumed 20 mana after the discounts and boosts from his progress and prodigy titles. Clearly the enchantments on the staff to amplify mana were far more efficient than his method at this point. Still, he had his first offensive ability and had managed to create it entirely on his own. He was somewhat curious why the new skill had improved his wisdom though.
“So why do things like creating a new ability or evolving my meditation skill improve my wisdom?” He turned his eyes to the Guide as he asked the question.
“As I explained earlier, wisdom is linked to both your intuition and your ability to understand esoterica. The ability you created was not forged out of your knowledge of magical theory,” The Guide explained. “It was assembled from your experience with the staff you used and you own intuitive grasp of mana manipulation, ergo it was a display of your wisdom, not your intelligence. Meditation is about introspection, and the form of meditation you have learned so far is deeply tied to your grasp of mana, therefore it, too, is tied to your wisdom.”
